oc:kn_0222f6cf a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building a new slash command from scratch" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Start with single-responsibility command without frontmatter 2. Test that basic invocation works 3. Add frontmatter (description, allowed-tools) 4. Add argument-hint if needed 5. Add model override for cost/speed tuning 6. Provide usage examples in comments" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Incremental development catches issues early and avoids debugging complex command definitions" ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_21b0d33c a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating commands that take user input" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Always include argument-hint in frontmatter when commands accept arguments, and document expected usage patterns." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Without argument hints, users and the agent cannot discover or correctly invoke the command" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_6c898770 a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing any command frontmatter and body" ;
    oc:codeLanguage "markdown" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use frontmatter fields: description, allowed-tools, argument-hint, model. Reference arguments with $1, $2 or $ARGUMENTS. Reference files with @$filepath. Embed shell commands with !`command`." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These are the core syntax primitives for Claude Code slash commands" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_9ad1b4fe a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When authoring command body text" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Do not write commands as messages TO users. Commands are instructions FOR Claude — they tell the agent what to do, not what the user will see." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Confusing audience direction leads to commands that narrate instead of execute" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_9cf185c1 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing any new slash command" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Each command should have single responsibility and a clear purpose — start basic without frontmatter, then add complexity incrementally." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Single-responsibility commands are easier to test, maintain, and compose into larger workflows" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_a249b9b1 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating any slash command" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Commands are stored as .md files in .claude/commands/ directory. File name becomes the slash command name (e.g., review.md → /review)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Convention-based discovery requires correct file placement and naming" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_a5554e4d a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When deciding command structure for a new use case" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Seven proven patterns cover most needs: Read-Only Analysis (Read+Grep), Git Operations (Bash(git:*)), Single Argument ($1), Multiple Arguments ($1 $2), Fast Execution (model: haiku), File Comparison (@$1 vs @$2), Context Gathering (shell output + file refs)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Reusing proven patterns reduces design time and ensures commands work correctly" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_e804f8d3 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When configuring command frontmatter" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use model: haiku for fast, repetitive tasks; model: sonnet for analysis/research tasks. Restrict allowed-tools to minimum needed (Read+Grep for read-only, Bash(git:*) for git operations)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Right-sizing the model and tool access reduces cost, improves speed, and limits blast radius" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

